Closing Statement

SIL explores a fundamental possibility:

Motion can emerge from structure — without reliance on time, order, or synchronization.

It is released openly to encourage:

independent validation
real-world testing
safe experimentation
broader adoption of structure-first motion systems

Where motion is traditionally governed by sequence and time,
SIL demonstrates that it can also be understood as a process of structural resolution.

SIL is offered as a reference model for that shift.
